<TITLE> Public works ministry staff killed in city </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 7 (bdnews24.com)  A public works ministry employee was killed at East Monipur of Mirpur in the capital on Tuesday morning. The dead was Raquibul Islam Mukul aka Yousuf, 35. He was a draftsman working with the public works city development directorate. Mirpur police chief Nazim Uddin told bdnews24.com that the murder occurred at around 8:15am. He suspected previous enmity behind the murder. According to the locals' statements, the police official said, as Raquibul left home to go to his office Tuesday morning, a group of youths took him away a little distance off, killed him and left the place. Police found an injury behind Raquibul's head. "We are looking into the matter," he said. The body was sent to the Dhaka Medical College Hospital morgue, the police official added. bd
